    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Condenser Core</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Anytime the refrigerant system is opened, the lubricant in the system must be replaced after the
                    system is reassembled. The amount of lubricant, and the method of adding it to the system, varies
                    based on the service performed on the system. To determine the correct amount of lubricant
                    (refrigerant oil), refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603007.xml" xrefid="hl1603007">OIL FILL GUIDELINES</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Anytime an A/C fitting is disconnected, the O-ring must be replaced. The new O-ring must be
                    lubricated with mineral-based oil (International P/N ZGGR725008). Never use grease, penetrating oil,
                    motor oil, ester or PAG oil, etc. to lubricate O-rings and fittings.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Installation of a new receiver/drier is not required when repairing the air conditioning system,
                    except:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>when there is physical evidence of system contamination from a failed A/C compressor;
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>when there is damage to the receiver/drier;</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>or, when the quantity of refrigerant oil retained in the system cannot otherwise be
                            accurately determined.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Recover the refrigerant. For additional information, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603003.xml" xrefid="hl1603003">DISCHARGING THE SYSTEM (REFRIGERANT
                    RECOVERY)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the condenser inlet and outlet lines. Cap all openings until ready to
                reinstall.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Discard the O-ring seals.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To install, tighten to 33 Nm (24 lbf-ft).</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the A/C condenser pusher fan electrical connector.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201050" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0034575.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 29.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 4 nuts and the A/C condenser pusher fan.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201051" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0034574.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 30.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 4 condenser mounting nuts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201052" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020020.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px"/>
            <caption>Figure 31.</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the condenser core.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Install new O-ring seals.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Evacuate, leak test and charge the refrigerant system. For additional information, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16030_HL1603005.xml" xrefid="hl1603005">EVACUATING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
